MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8

Add three new madvise behavior constants for AI inference KV-cache
device control planes:

  MADV_KV_HOT      (104) -- the specified range contains KV blocks
                            actively used in a decode loop; a registered
                            device handler should set their eviction
                            priority to the maximum value

  MADV_KV_EVICT    (105) -- the specified range of KV blocks is no
                            longer needed by the caller; a registered
                            device handler should schedule them for
                            immediate background migration to a lower
                            memory tier

  MADV_KV_PREFETCH (106) -- hint to a registered device handler that
                            the caller is at decode step t and desires
                            a prefetch lookahead of W steps; aux data
                            is encoded in the length field (high 32
                            bits = W, low 32 bits = t) per RFC
                            convention described in patch 3/4

Values 104-106 are chosen to follow directly after the guard page values
102-103 (MADV_GUARD_INSTALL, MADV_GUARD_REMOVE) added in v6.13.

The four architectures (alpha, mips, parisc, xtensa) that define their
own mman.h overrides for the 100-series range are updated identically to
match the generic header, following the exact same pattern used by the
MADV_GUARD_INSTALL/REMOVE additions in commit <guard-page-commit>.

The tools/ mirror header is also updated so that kselftest and perf can
reference these constants without pulling in the kernel headers directly.

Signed-off-by: Manish Keshav Lachwani <mlachwani@gmail.com>
